<p>Trellis is a pure Lean library with minimal dependencies. No native code or special build scripts are required.</p>

<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://lean-lang.org/">Lean 4</a> (v4.26.0+)</li>
  <li>Lake (included with Lean)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Lakefile Configuration</h3>

<p>Add Trellis to your <code>lakefile.lean</code>:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">require trellis from git "https://github.com/nathanial/trellis" @ "v0.0.1"</code></pre>

<h3>Building</h3>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Build the library
lake build

# Run tests
lake test</code></pre>

<h3>Dependencies</h3>

<p>Trellis has minimal dependencies:</p>

<table class="api-table">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Dependency</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>crucible</code></td><td>Test framework (dev dependency)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>chronos</code></td><td>Timing utilities (optional)</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Quick Verification</h3>

<p>After adding Trellis to your project, verify it works:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">import Trellis

open Trellis

-- Should compile successfully
def testLayout : LayoutResult :=
  layout (LayoutNode.leaf 1 ⟨100, 50⟩) 500 300</code></pre>

